<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Quiligotti
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Exceptional costs of Pounds 1.13m left Quiligotti, the USM-traded tiles and
flooring group, Pounds 1.27m in the red for the six months to September 30.
There were losses of Pounds 228,000 last time after an exceptional charge of
Pounds 80,000.
Turnover fell to Pounds 7.01m (Pounds 8.45m) and there was a trading loss of
Pounds 138,000 (Pounds 148,000).
The exceptional charge comprised further provisions against old contract
debtors and problem contracts, reorganisation costs, and management changes
relating to the placing and open offer and the acquisition of Chelsea Group.
The company said its strategy was to concentrate on the terrazzo floor tiles
business, and accordingly it was ending its activities in the ceramics area.
Losses per share deepened from 0.33p to 1.74p.
</TEXT>
