<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Break for the Border
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Higher costs of operating as a listed company since its flotation in May
reduced pre-tax profits at Break for the Border Group from Pounds 149,000 to
Pounds 140,000 for the six months to September 30.
Sales at the restaurant and nightclub operator rose to Pounds 1.95m (Pounds
1.87m). Gross profit came to Pounds 1.48m (Pounds 1.41m) but operating
expenses took Pounds 1.34m (Pounds 1.26m). Earnings per share came to 1.6p
(2.6p).
Mr Ian Howard, chief executive, pointed out that traditionally two thirds of
turnover came in the second half and the burden of overheads fell heavily on
the first half. As December was such an important month the company would
make a trading statement in January.
</TEXT>
