FT  10 DEC 93 / UK Company News: PSB resolutions rejected by ICD
shareholders
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
At the International Communication &amp; Data extraordinary general meeting held
yesterday, shareholders defeated all resolutions put forward by PSB, which
requisitioned the meeting and claims to control 23.6 per cent of ICD's
voting rights, for the removal of a majority of the existing directors and
their replacement by PSB nominees.
The resolutions were defeated by about 33m votes (58 per cent) to about 24m
votes (42 per cent).
On Wednesday, IMC, the USM-quoted soft drinks and leisure group, exercised
its option to subscribe for 6.95m shares at 7p in ICD, the marketing
services company.
