FT  10 DEC 93 / World News in Brief: Gales sweep Europe
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gales lashed northern Europe, killing at least 13 people in Britain alone. A
fisherman was lost from a Dutch trawler in the North Sea, and an Irish
rescue helicopter lifted five seamen from a Spanish trawler which foundered
in the Atlantic. Picture, Page 6
