FT  10 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Resort Hotels gets extension for accounts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Resort Hotels, shares in which were suspended in mid-July, has said it will
be unable to present its accounts for the year to April 30 at the annual
meeting on December 31.
It said the accounts would be considered at an extraordinary meeting some
time after the annual meeting. It had obtained from the trade and industry
secretary an extension of the period allowed for delivering the accounts
until February 28 1994.
It hoped soon to be able to give details of the group's financial position
and events that led to the suspension.
