FT  10 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Hiscox launches new Lloyd's investment
trust
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Hiscox Syndicates, the Lloyd's managing agents, yesterday announced that it
had raised Pounds 11.2m to form a new Lloyd's investment trust, Hiscox
Dedicated.
Applications under an offer for subscription were received for 2,240,600
units.
Accordingly 11,203,000 partly paid ordinary shares and 2,240,600 warrants
have been allotted.
Hiscox Dedicated had been seeking to raise up to Pounds 25m, but Mr Robert
Hiscox, a director of the new trust, said he was 'pleased to have achieved
an application level significantly in excess of the minimum, because Hiscox
Dedicated was launched after a large number of other Lloyd's funds had
already approached the capital market for investment.'
The Roberts &amp; Hiscox members agency raised Pounds 30m for the Hiscox Select
Insurance Fund in October.
The trust is one of the most popular of the 11 Lloyd's investment vehicles
currently listed on the stock exchange and is trading at a premium to its
net asset value.
Charterhouse Tilney Securities, which placed the issue, has informed Hiscox
Dedicated that it expects a matched bargain facility to be available for the
investment trust under the stock exchange rule 535(2).
