</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mercury Asset Management said yesterday it had raised Pounds 425.8m for its
World Mining Trust, making it the largest ever investment trust launch in
the UK.
A total of 380m shares had been placed - with warrants attached on a 1-for-5
basis - with institutions and others. A further 45.8m shares were applied
for under the public offer, and will be allocated in full.
The trust, which will be managed by Mr Julian Baring, will invest in
companies which produce gold and base metals. Dealings are expected to start
on December 15.
