<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 93 / Technology (Worth Watching): Core IT elements kept in-house
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Companies are increasingly happy to outsource their information technology
requirements. However, contrary to popular perception, they did not
outsource core facilities but peripheral ones, according to the latest
report, 'UK IT Outsourcing Survey: 1993', from the PA Consulting Group. The
report surveyed 230 UK organisations, 74 per cent of which had outsourced
some of their IT provision. On average only 10 per cent of their IT budget
was spent on outsourced services.
Although 55 per cent of the companies cited cost savings as a main reason
for outsourcing, 30 per cent said there had been none. In some cases costs
had even risen. PA: UK, 071 730 9000.
</TEXT>
