<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 93 / Technology (Worth Watching): Hollywood on a desk-top disc
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Technology developed for the big Hollywood film studios has now been shrunk
to suit the needs of companies which use desk-top publishing or applications
that involve moving video images.
Microdisk, developed by Micropolis of Chatsworth, California, is a hard disc
drive which delivers an uninterrupted flow of data, unlike many other hard
discs. It was specially developed for use in film studios, as video images
need a continuous data flow.
The desk-top version - a board and a disc drive - sell for less than Pounds
10,000 and can be used with a PC or Macintosh. Micropolis: US, 818 709 3300;
UK, 0734 751315.
</TEXT>
