<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 93 / Auditors receive Cadbury code guide
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Auditors will be required to highlight any aspects of non-compliance with
the Cadbury code of corporate governance that companies fail to list, under
guidelines published yesterday.
They must produce a statement drawing attention to any departures from the
code not flagged in a statement by the directors, according to a bulletin
issued by the Auditing Practices Board (APB), the standard-setting body for
the profession.
The advice is preliminary because detailed guidance is still being developed
on two areas recommended in the Cadbury code. They are commentaries on
internal controls and on whether the company is a 'going concern'.
Meanwhile, the APB strongly advises auditors not to make any comments on
these aspects of the code.
It says auditors are not required to perform additional procedures to
investigate the appropriateness of non-compliance. They should review all
meetings, question directors and attend audit committee meetings as part of
