auditor would disregard it at his peril.'
The guidance came into effect immediately. Companies must provide a
statement of compliance with the Cadbury code for accounting periods after
June 30 this year.
Somers Baker, a small London-based accountancy firm, is to face scrutiny
from the accountancy profession's highest disciplinary body for its role as
auditor and adviser to War on Want, the campaigning third world charity.
The firm was criticised for its work in a report published by the Charity
Commission in 1991, and paid Pounds 309,500 to War on Want in an
out-of-court settlement in August this year.
The investigation is to be conducted by Mr Michael Chance, executive counsel
of the Joint Disciplinary Scheme, which represents the Institutes of
Chartered Accountants in England and Wales, and Scotland, and the Chartered
Association of Certified Accountants.
The scheme only examines serious issues that command a high level of public
interest. Only three investigations are currently under way: into Barlow
Clowes, the Bank of Credit and Commerce International and the Maxwell
affair.
Disclosures Relating to Corporate Governance. Accountancy Books, PO Box 620,
