</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The private sector has had far less success winning council contracts in
Scotland than in England and Wales, the Local Government Management Board
says. No private contractors have won school catering contracts or cleaning
contracts, other than building cleaning, in Scotland.
In its strongest sector, building cleaning, the private sector won 18.7 per
cent of contracts. In England and Wales, 54.6 per cent of such contracts
went to the private sector.
