<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 93 / Gabon president retains power
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Troops with tanks patrolled the streets of Libreville last night as the
Gabon government announced President Omar Bongo had won an absolute majority
in Sunday's multi-party elections, retaining the post he has held for 26
years, AP reports. Officials said he avoided a run-off election by winning
51.07 per cent of the vote, against 27 per cent for his nearest rival, Roman
Catholic priest Paul Mba Abessole.
