<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 93 / Drogoul jailed for 37 months
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Christopher Drogoul, the former banker accused of funnelling around
Dollars 5bn (Pounds 3.3bn) in illegal loans to help arm Iraq during the
1980s, was sentenced to 37 months' imprisonment yesterday.
The former Atlanta branch manager of Italy's Banca Nazionale del Lavoro, Mr
Drogoul has consistently claimed the Italian and US governments were fully
aware the money was being channelled to Iraq. He claimed the BNL Atlanta
branch had been 'a tool of the US government'.
Mr Drogoul, 44, had pleaded guilty to two charges of filing fraudulent
reports to the Federal Reserve and one of wire fraud, as part of a plea
agreement under which more serious charges of bank fraud were dropped. Hehas
already spent 20 months in jail, reducing his term to 17 months.
</TEXT>
