FT  09 DEC 93 / Nato to plan for a wider role
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WHITE, Defence Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A new Nato command system enabling allies to send task forces for
peacekeeping and other missions outside their own territory is due to be
drawn up within six months, writes David White, Defence Correspondent, in
Brussels.
A US-inspired Combined Joint Task Forces scheme, which would involve setting
up 'flexible' headquarters able to deploy ad hoc forces is set to be
formally approved by allied leaders at their Brussels summit on January
10-11. Nato military authorities will be asked to present detailed plans to
ministers by June.
The scheme reflects growing emphasis on Nato's ability to act more
effectively in crises such as the former Yugoslavia.
Crucial to the scheme would be the participation of France and Spain, which
belong to Nato but keep their forces outside the alliance's mainstream
military structure.
